OL,6,F"It protects key services. It begins
OL,7,Fto repair the council's finances. It
OL,8,Fstarts to reduce debt, and it does so
OL,9,Fwithout placing unnecessary additional
OL,10,Fburdens on the people of Kent.
OL,12,F"There is more to do. There will be
OL,13,Ftough decisions ahead, but for the
OL,14,Ffirst time in many years, this council
OL,15,Fis moving in the right direction."
OL,17,FAdult social care and health is "one
OL,18,Fof the most critical threats to the
OL,19,Fcouncil's financial resilience" with
OL,20,Fan estimated annual #68 million risk,
OL,21,Fbudget documents show.
